  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Piccolo is small by name and small by nature. There's just 19 rooms but it's packed with personality. The Ongari and Deflorian families who run the hotel will quickly make you feel at home. It's in a lovely quiet position that catches the best of the sun and it only takes ten minutes or so if you fancy strolling into <a data-udi="umb://document/4b1a446ce5904ac5997483a5477c9c8c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4b1a446ce5904ac5997483a5477c9c8c}" title="Val di Fassa (Canazei &amp; Campitello)">Canazei</a>. The main Belvedere gondola is a little further on and you can use the shuttle service to and from the lift. </p>
<h2>Cosy hotel</h2>
<p>The cosy lounge bar area is the perfect place to socialise and catch up after the day in the mountains, especially when they provide free afternoon tea and cake each day. The large dining room is the main hub of the hotel where you'll be treated to tasty dinners that are prepared with great care and the best ingredients. In true Landin tradition they'll encourage you to relax and take it slow. Give yourself time to enjoy the food, while they look after you. </p>
<h2>Unwind and relax</h2>
<p>Having access to the wellness centre is ideal for when you need that little boost of energy when you get back from the slopes. Relax in the Finnish sauna or the Turkish bath, it does wonders for those tired ski legs and leaves you in prime condition for getting out and exploring the next day. There's also a salt water pool and a whirlpool which are both great for rejuvenating.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Piccolo the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
